Elytra (EL/EW 0.59–0.69) much wider than long, trapezoidal; each elytron with two basal foveae; discal stria distinct, extending to posterior third. Mesoventrite (
Fig. 5D
) with median setose area narrow; setose area about 1/5 as wide as mesoventral width; lateral mesoventral foveae glabrous; metaventrite coarsely punctate at middle, convex, but area just above metaventral apex roundly impressed; that impression half as long as metaventral length, about 0.3 times wider than metaventral width; anterior margin of that impression demarcated from other part of metaventrite. Legs with each femora broadest near middle; protibiae straight; mesotibiae arcuate at apical fourth; metatibiae (
Fig. 5E
) nearly straight, each mesal margin with slight laminate plate; each tarsi (
Fig. 5F
) with tarsomere 2 two-thirds as long as tarsomere 3; tarsal claws each asymmetrical in size; posterior claws thin, short.
